Let's Play Viva Piñata
KeybadeBlox
Title
column7: Description

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 1: Welcome, have some worthless junk
column7: I feel like the whole "prison island" idea is actually a pretty good explanation for why all the stuff we're given is so incredibly horrid.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 2: The donut of life
column7: A story of life's beginning and end all in the span of a few brief minutes.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 3: Growing the garden
column7: Things are starting to take shape already, if just a little bit.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 4: New neighbours
column7: These things just don't stop coming.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 5: Sweet and sour
column7: New piñatas, new town members, so many new things, and we've been playing for a while.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 6: Stuck Seedos
column7: This guy has problems.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 7: Get off my corn
column7: I'm seriously worried about Seedos at this point.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 8:  What is wrong with Corn Corner
column7: Why does everyone get stuck there?  We also kind of abuse a piñata or two, but it profits us in the end, so it's okay.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 9: Life and death
column7: Learning more about the harshness of reality every day, I suppose.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 10: Stumbling into money
column7: It almost feels like I cheated with how much I got from that, but it's not really like I accidentally exploited anything.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 11: Bigger and better
column7: I'm not sure I need this added responsibility right now.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 12: Greater greenery
column7: We got to it eventually, at least.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 13: Getting pretty
column7: About time we put some real effort into the aesthetics.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 14: Technical difficulties
column7:
And I thought it was bad when my SSX 3 disc stopped working when I was recording it.  Details on what happened and what will happen are below:

After some investigation, it seems like my 360's graphics card is failing.  At the moment, I can start the console, and then it dies after a few minutes regardless of what I do, so it's pretty much dead.  I've been wanting a modded 360 for quite a while now but lack the resources to install custom firmware on one myself (although the old one also had a disc drive I flashed on my own), so I'm thinking I'll buy a modded 360 with a bigger hard drive (since this one has a puny 20GB HDD).  If all goes well, I should have it up and running in about two weeks, but I'll have to move on to another (probably short) game in the meantime.  On the bright side, having an updated and modded 360 will mean being able to play all 360 games, including Trouble in Paradise, and play modded original Xbox games, which I had a huge idea for years ago that I really want to execute one day.  Lots of appreciation to the 360 that lasted me well over a decade, though.

I knew this playthrough would have a decent amount of life and death, but I didn't think it'd extend into this sort of thing.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 15: Back to life
column7: A new day with a new 360.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 16: The Beggar
column7: Nice to get a proper introduction to him now, I suppose.  I think we actually know the whole cast now, if I remember right.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 17: A fresh start
column7: It's about time we got to a garden with a more consistent aesthetic.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 18: Digging a hole
column7: This is the kind of work one does as a punishment.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 19: Bringing in life
column7: Finally, some stuff that's actually alive.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 20: Massive seedage
column7: I wonder where Seedos's weak point is.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 21: Aggression
column7: Why can't we just get along?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 22: The right garden for the job
column7: Definitely can't get everything done in one place.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 23: Lovely
column7: Need to get those master romancer awards.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 24: An all-powerful and self-important anglerfish
column7:
Never noticed that Ivor's alerts had the wrong face, actually.

Actually turns out that the anglerfish thing is a reference to Banjo-Tooie.  Nice little easter egg.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 25: Romance everywhere
column7: I'm not sure I realized as I was recording this how I was basically trying to breed everything at once.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 26: Checking in
column7: Just making sure I have my plans for Paper Pets in order for a future garden, mostly.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 27: Tafflies are the worst
column7: Why did I decide to get master romancer for these, again?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 28: Sweet farewells
column7: Not just because they're filled with candy, either.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 29: Ducks everywhere
column7: Master romancing really takes over a whole garden by the end, doesn't it?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 30: Gardening by satellite
column7: I actually do think that this particular watering can is a downgrade of sorts, so the sooner we get the next one, the better.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 31: The accident
column7: I can't say I've ever gotten a piñata by accident like that.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 32: The humongous house
column7: Unrelated, but man, this game's soundtrack is so nice when I hear it in post.  I wish I noticed it more while playing.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 33: On-site research
column7: I'm mostly working off of memory, but taking the occasional chance to refresh it helps keep things running smoothly, I think.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 34: The forlorn corn
column7: Now I have to wait two weeks to see whether I can save it or not.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 35: A late introduction
column7: ...where these guys not supposed to have appeared yet?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 36: Feeling like I'm forgetting something
column7: Something yellow and grainy.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 37: Digging a(nother) hole
column7: Really just expanding the first hole.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 38: The long-awaited guest
column7: Our digging finally starts to pay off.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 39: Last few scoops
column7: I have to say, I'm kind of proud of how this garden turned out.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 40: Coming for the corn
column7: And to think we almost forgot.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 41: Expansion
column7: Cleaning up the new garden space really took more time than I had thought it would.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 42: Going green
column7: I do have to say that it feels so wonderfully open when the full garden space is filled with grass like this.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 43: The watering can
column7: I actually really like this game's progression of watering cans, but man do I wish the second-last one wasn't worse than all the others.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 44: Everybody's on fire
column7: Why wasn't this a problem before?  At least I have a new watering can to put them out with.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 45: Starting the farm
column7: Having hit a bit of a lull, it's time to start up our big business venture.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 46: Bees!
column7: Come to think of it, taming a raccoon is probably the wrong way to start up a farm.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 47: The chicken coop
column7: It might seem small, but let's just pretend it's like the cluckles house and is actually way bigger on the inside than it looks.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 48: Hurling towards financial ruin
column7: Let's hope we see a return on this investment quickly.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 49: Accidental time travel
column7: Happy accident, I guess?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 50: The cycle of poverty
column7: Times like these make you realize just how generous Seedos is, at least.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 51: The picky profitamole
column7: Why red, specifically?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 52: Back on the farm
column7: With actual money this time!

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 53: Growing the farm
column7: In the literal sense of piñatas and plants growing, I mean.  Definitely beats buying everything.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 54: Flat honey
column7: I bet you Lottie's going to run off somewhere and sell it for thousands of chocolate coins as a novelty despite how little she paid for it.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 55: Déjà Vu
column7: ...I don't know why things seem to be happening out of order.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 56: The big guy
column7: And now everybody keeps getting stepped on.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 57: Cheering up
column7: Not sure why Julie was so much unhappier than the others, honestly.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 58: Sandwich house call
column7: I don't know why Bart doesn't just sell sandwiches at his own place.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 59: The numbers lie
column7: At least it's not as bad as with the chippo, but why can't this game just be honest?  Between this and Leafos, it's like you can't trust anything.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 60: Free range ghost sheep
column7: I guess I really had no choice.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 61: Going green
column7: Guess we needed grass eventually.  No idea what's up with that macaracoon, though.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 62: Guests that do not belong
column7: ...and now piñatas are just coming in regardless of their visit requirements?  I'm legitimately wondering if something's bugged about my game.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 63: Spoiled cows
column7: The things these piñatas ask for are starting to get ridiculous.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 64: The most stereotypical cat
column7: This cat seriously checks every box for stereotypical things to like eating.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 65: "Thumping great talons"
column7: They look more like little stubs to me.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 66: Incurring Lottie's wrath
column7: She doesn't seem to have the patience for contemplative customers.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 67: Getting grassy
column7: I'm going to lose so many things in that grass.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 68: Putting the wood in the woods
column7: All that grass needed some variety anyways.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 69: Hard to please
column7: We are going to need so many berries.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 70: Hitting the ground running
column7: Nice to see that we're making progress way more quickly all of a sudden.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 71: Walking the line
column7: Why do untamed piñatas have to taunt you from right outside your garden?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 72: Educated mistreatment
column7: It would certainly be quite the experience figuring this sort of thing out on your own.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 73: Bonboon vs. Syrupent, Round 1
column7: This is the beginning of what will surely be a long rivalry.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 74: The doenut episode
column7: As if their "disco" joint wasn't enough, the doenuts just hog the spotlight for most of this episode, too.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 75: Round 2
column7: It's Tina's turn now.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 76: If two heads are better than one...
column7: I still don't get that dance.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 77: Making him wait
column7: Staying in that pose for two and a half minutes must make your arms tired.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 78: Here to educate
column7: Took this guy long enough to show his face, except for those few times he talked to us before.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 79: Saturated with toxins
column7: I think we just permanently intoxicated a piñata.  This game has a strange sense of humour.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 80: For the monkeys
column7: All sorts of trees going on now, and new piñatas with them.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 81: Ants all over
column7: Time to get started on the chain of piñatas to finally let those fourheads breed.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 82: And suddenly dancing
column7: Not romance dancing, either.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 83: Bringing in the bugs
column7: Tafflies, raisants, arocknids, buzzlegums...

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 84: Stuck in a tree
column7: It would really be nice if you could call a pinata down from a tree.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 85: House arrest
column7: I feel like this game should prevent you from placing structures where piñatas will get stuck upon exiting.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 86: Playing keepaway
column7: Why does everybody want to eat this but the ones that actually need to eat it?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 87: Getting colourful
column7: We've kind of been neglecting colour variants lately.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 88: No appreciation
column7: You'd think they'd care to give something in return for me giving them so many things to eat.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 89: Flying piñatas are the worst
column7: Even after I swore off breeding them, they still make my life worse.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 90: The takeover
column7: The many mighty fourheads, with nearly thirty heads between them all.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 91: Not enough room for the two of us
column7: If garden space worked like stocks, the 65% ownership touted by these fourheads would be quite powerful.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 92: Back on the farm
column7: All that money has opened up some new doors to us.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 93: Feeding the cats
column7: I guess eating the milk's bottle is just what piñatas do.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 94: Dress-up
column7: We take interest in clothes.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 95: Making cat eggs
column7: So are no piñatas actually mammals?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 96: Displaced by dogs
column7: That's probably the easiest romance we've had in a while.  I find myself really not liking barkbarks for some reason, though.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 97: Done with the dogs
column7: Time to make room for more farm animals.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 98: A mystery
column7: Let's not worry about that building mishap for now.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 99: Lessons in loving
column7: A little dumb that I hadn't realized what I was missing in those romance games until now.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 100: "Happy" hundred
column7: We have a special visitor for our hundredth episode.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 101: Pony and pig party
column7: Wouldn't be a farm without raising livestock, I suppose.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 102: One done
column7: About time we actually finished up a garden for once.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 103: Back to the bog
column7: This place is much more high-maintenance than I remembered.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 104: Dragging it out
column7: We're going to have to be a bit more efficient if we're going to finish this game any time soon.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 105: Threat neutralized
column7: I guess all you really need to keep ruffians from breaking your stuff is a slight incline.  Unfortunately for me, you can't really make hills in this game (though I do want that now).

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 106: Coacoadile cravings
column7: At least I make some profit off of feeding piñatas to each other.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 107: More flying piñata foofery
column7: In my dream Viva Piñata, flying piñatas literally just wouldn't exist.  There'd probably be different settings for gardens, too.  Maybe one that's underwater.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 108: Wanton destruction
column7: We might've disabled a ruffian, but there are apparently other things that can wreck your stuff.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 109: Cocoadile companions
column7: No idea what we're going to do about those dragumflies, honestly.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 110: Prof. Pester, Part 2
column7: I get pretty fed up with that guy.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 111: The garden keeps growing
column7: Somehow, even after all this time, we're still adding more and more residents to this pond.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 112: Bringing in the bugs
column7: Time for the dragumflies to be the centre of our world for a bit, I guess.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 113: The wait
column7: I'm sure that the stupidity with this buzzlegum is somehow related to the fact that it flies.  It's always the flying piñatas.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 114: The wait is over
column7: It's nice when things work out.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 115: Bye to the bog (for now)
column7: With it probably being the single garden we've put the most work into, it's interesting to see it "complete," so to speak.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 116: An actual garden
column7: About time we got to that "garden garden" I kept talking about.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 117: Bringing in the butterflies
column7: Or at least trying, because piñatas with fulfilled visit requirements apparently just don't care half the time.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 118: The best variant
column7: It's weird that variants with multiple colours are so rare, but I like it way more than the other solid ones.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 119: Mixing and matching
column7: Time to bring on the many different flutterscotches.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 120: Making the garden a garden
column7: Little details like a few flowerbeds can be a real help, I feel.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 121: Bigger and better flowers
column7: This is definitely the time and place to finally break out the really nice ones.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 122: Provisional plants
column7: We finally catch the interest of somebody new, too.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 123: Greed
column7: That fudgehog just up and takes what could be very useful for the other fudgehog instead.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 124: Pleased by the colours
column7: Someone really likes all the flutterscotch stuff we have going on.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 125: The wrong idea
column7: Turns out I had forgotten what candaries were this entire time.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 126: Banana neglect
column7: Why would they even create a piñata that won't fulfill its resident requirements given the necessary resources?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 127: Little things add up
column7: Small expenses add up to make me lose money, that is, not in any positive sense.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 128: Unhygienic housing
column7: I'm surprised that the encyclopaedia doesn't comment on the horrible hygiene of living in a building covered in your own excrement.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 129: More done, more to do
column7: It feels like every bit of progress is met with so much more to do, even though we're supposedly done with a good majority of the game.  There's even a garden or two we haven't really started on yet.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 130: Going on a journey
column7: The quest for a TV remote.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 131: Finally had their fill
column7: A day that we thought would never come is finally here, but there's still plenty left to do, of course.  I also realize now how to sell accessories, by the way.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 132: Back to building
column7: Lots of houses all of a sudden, somehow.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 133: Taking inventory
column7: Good to step back and get a good look at what's still left for us to do.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 134: Doing our research
column7: One must be an informed gardener.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 135: The hunger strike
column7: I still just don't get why nobody's eating what they're supposed to eat.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 136: The distraction
column7: What I thought was progress provided to us by a certain hunter only made life harder.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 137: Inexplicable anger
column7: I would guess that the thistles have something to do with it, but I don't see anyone getting zapped by them.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 138: A small victory
column7: Every bit of progress is cherished when it's this hard to come by.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 139: One step forward, two steps back
column7: Having finally acquired immense amounts of wealth, we find out that a certain someone has decided to forget the previous favours we've done them, and we discover the consequences of thoughtless deforestation.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 140: A real plan
column7: I finally figure out how to get out of our rut of waiting for the piñatas t come to us.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 141: Patience wins out
column7: It took way more work than it should have, though.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 142: Colours of all sorts
column7: Nice to have one of our big tasks out of the way now.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 143: A couple new couples
column7: Romancing a few new piñatas has definitely been a long time coming.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 144: Overcrowding
column7: I actually still don't feel particularly sure about how this game determines whether your garden is too full or not, considering how inconsistent it is.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 145: Additional decoration
column7: If we're not going to tend to the flowerbeds, we might as well have some plants that don't require our attention.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 146: Finally got you
column7: We had to drag them here by force, but they're finally here.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 147: One done
column7: Feels real nice to finally have a garden definitively finished.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 148: Counterproductive housing
column7: Requiring so much water but having a house that requires so much land is frustratingly paradoxical.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 149: Unrelenting depression
column7: I'm sure it's somehow because that flutterscotch is a flying piñata.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 150: Upgrades!  ...whatever they do
column7: Not even the wikia seems to know what shovel handle upgrades actually do.  They say the platinum one lets you dig water faster, but it looks the same to me.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 151: Another one done
column7: Progress feels pretty good, I have to say.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 152: Horrible hunters
column7: How do these pretztails not just starve?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 153: The list keeps getting longer
column7: As we resort to getting more and more piñatas from Gretchem, I can only wonder how I ever 100%'d this game without her the first time.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 154: Better late than never
column7: Weird that it took us so long to get around to even building a house for such a low-level species.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 155: Back and forth
column7: Not sure why I flip-flopped between which species to breed first.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 156: Actual seizure warning
column7: You might want to skip the romance dance in this one, even if just to avoid a headache.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 157: The dwindling fortune
column7: And it took so much work to reach 100k, too.  Guess there's no point if we don't spend it, though.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 158: More upon more
column7: I don't know how it is that constantly adding more and more piñatas to this garden hasn't caused any real problems yet.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 159: It happened again
column7: Thankfully, it doesn't seem to be so catastrophic this time.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 160: Awkward pause
column7: Weird way to end a romance dance.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 161: Twycross, England
column7: I somehow skipped over the fact that Rare is actually based in Twycross.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 162: Diving into fantasy
column7: We also discover something rather peculiar about bonboons and their fight-stopping abilities.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 163: Envious equines
column7: Y'know, for being the mascot of the series, the horstachio's really self-absorbed and whatnot.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 164: The moat
column7: It'll probably become one later, at least.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 165: Big piñata, big appetite
column7: At least they don't have expensive tastes.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 166: Corn explosion
column7: Maybe the game only lets you plant a few seeds at a time because it couldn't handle an explosion of more than ten corns at once.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 167: Digging for treasure
column7: I still think it's a silly and ultimately useless attachment, but I guess we might as well use the chocolate sniffer.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 168: Freak of nature
column7: The world evidently just can't stand its existence.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 169: Let there be horses
column7: Fitting enough that the mascot should get some screentime, I suppose.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 170: Finally fantastic
column7: Another one of the centrepieces of our "fantasy" garden has finally arrived.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 171: Replaced
column7: I never liked that particular species anyways.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 172: Grotesquely large
column7: Some piñatas really do manage to take over your entire garden when you try to please them.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 173: A sour taste
column7: Let's see if we can make this turn out better than last time.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 174: Coming out to play
column7: With our life free of sours, the last piñata to appear rears its face.  That's not to say it's the last piñata we'll encounter, of course.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 175: Not so tranquil
column7: You'd think a creature that symbolizes peace and harmony would be better at avoiding conflict.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 176: Master romancer
column7: To be honest, I actually don't mind the master romancing in this game all too much, since it makes you a massive profit anyways.  It's probably good that the game pushes you to do it.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 177: The slaughter
column7: Those few minutes of unprecedented violence turned out to be quite productive.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 178: Castle construction
column7: I literally designed this garden around this house, and it's still massively disruptive.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 179: Fluffy clouds
column7: The fantasy garden finally begins to take shape.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 180: The royal metal detector
column7: I really can't tell if being able to set off the horns like that is intentional or not.  It seems to only work if you're holding metal, but then how are the piñatas making it go off, too?  Do they have metal in them?

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 181: The royal tithe
column7: These guys are pretty demanding, if they're literally asking for their subjects' first born.  And second, for that matter.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 182: Finished fantasy
column7: There's actually something small I forgot to do here for an achievement, so we'll briefly come back eventually, but we've got other things to do now.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 183: The badlands
column7: A garden for those that have nowhere else to be.  About as opposite the fantasy garden as you can get.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 184: The one we forgot
column7: I might have forgotten about this piñata until now, but at least it's incredibly appropriate for this garden.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 185: Heating up
column7: Scenery makes a big difference, so all the better to have a hot and dry building for a hot and dry garden.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 186: Out of a job
column7: Our workers end up too productive for their own good, and now their employment is on thin ice.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 187: Loose lips
column7: That worker said the wrong thing at the wrong time.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 188: Old problems come anew
column7: After all this time, there's still not really anything we can do if piñatas just won't come into the garden.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 189: Keeping watch
column7: Finally, a helper other than the diggerling that's actually useful.  ...unless you have the Tower of Sour and the captain's cutlass, that is.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 190: Slacking off
column7: Our workers disappoint us.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 191: One by one
column7: Nobody can say we're not making progress, at least.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 192: Sabotage
column7: Our workers give us more grief.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 193: Shopping for food
column7: These late game piñatas have some serious appetites.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 194: The last straw
column7: Somebody's been causing us too many problems.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 195: The disco
column7: I only just now noticed that the jukebox in that romance dance is both extremely small and facing the wrong way.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 196: Hard to please seed
column7: It would be nice if the game told me how much space I need for an oak tree.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 197: Hunting season
column7: I'm probably Gretchem's favourite customer at this point.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 198: Waiting game
column7: We wait on Gretchem, and we wait on feral piñatas.  At least we're making progress regardless.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 199: Dwindling resources
column7: I finally start really wondering if I have enough money (or piñatas of a certain species, for that matter) to get everything done.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 200: Craving chocolate
column7: We figure it's about time to start doing something about our dwindling funds, while we wait for other things to progress on their own.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 201: The gang's all here
column7: We've finally managed to get a particular type of reward for every piñata, but we're not done yet.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 202: Raising the dead
column7: That's definitely my favourite romance dance in the game.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 203: The fundraiser
column7: One last push to finance the last of the game.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 204: Self defence
column7: Our search for achievements leads us to something much better than a watchling for keeping out undesirables.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 205: The tree
column7: The cost of those things really adds up.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 206: Distraction
column7: It's honestly not a real useful ability in any capacity, but it's cool to see piñatas that can do something special.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 207: The last one
column7: Time to finally get the last romance award out of the way.

column2: Let's Play Viva Piñata, ep 208: Finally done
column7: Definitely went on a lot longer than I had ever intended, but here we are.  All done in under fifty hours, no less, which means we even did it quicker than the game expected.
